====================================================================================================
 C463-002                            Top Run Crane Enhancements                18/DEC/2025  10:14am
====================================================================================================

      Id          Description
      ----------  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      PE7-00-25   Program to design the crane bracket and stiffeners for top running crane.
      PE2-01-1    Maximum length of available web and flanges on W member type can provide multiple plates for endwall columns and rafters, rigid frame interior columns, and wind framing members.
      PE7-02-7    Multiple crane system layout can be entered as part of the building data entry.
      PE7-02-8    Program to design all crane runway beams, support beams, and support columns in a building.
      PE7-02-9    Program to detail and cost all crane runway beams, support beams, and support columns in a building.
      PE7-02-10   Building drawing is available for crane runway layout and identification of crane support members.
      PE7-05-2    Option to indicate the horizontal and vertical clearance requirements for crane systems in rigid frame design and detailing
      PE2-07-10   Option for slots in the bracket that supports the runway beams
      PE4-07-2    Rigid frame column web stiffener is detailed with a minimum width and hole for the attachment of crane runway beam longitudinal angle
      PE6-07-8    Crane drawing can show the part name for the individual parts used to make the combined runway beam sections
      PE8-11-2    Crane runway beam and cap channel can be specified by the user in the crane design input file
      PE5-12-4    Crane and runway beam weights are included in the total seismic weight for rigid frame design
      PE7-13-1    Crane beam stiffeners and lateral support angle detailing parameters may be separate from endwall parameters
      PE8-14-2    Crane runway beam lateral and longitudinal angle shop drawings are now provided
      PE5-20-3    Crane system members now have designed welds.  Also, runway beam channel can provide designed intermittent (stitch) welds.
      PE5-22-1    Crane support beam may be designed to support two crane runway beams.


